<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-33-0909 </DOCNO><TEXT>Viscosity reduction and swelling are the principal mechanisms contributedto the improvement of heavy-oil recovery by immiscible CO/sub 2/ displacement.This paper presents the results of experimental measurements for thephysical properties of heavy oils before and after CO/sub 2/ saturation.Based on measured data, correlations were developed for the predictionsof CO/sub 2/ solubility, oil swelling factor, and viscosity change forCO/sub 2/-saturated heavy oils.</TEXT></DOC>